===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[αερόπλανος]]''' (''aeroplanos'') "wandering in air", (referring to a "dreamer"), from '''[[αήρ]]''' (''aer'', genitive '''[[αέρος]]''' ''aeros'') "air" + '''[[πλάνη]]''' (''plane'') "wandering, ramble".

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{UK}} An [[airplane]]; a [[powered]] [[heavier-than-air]] [[aircraft]] with fixed [[wing]]s that obtains lift by the [[Bernoulli effect]] and is used for [[transportation]] of humans and goods; for [[amusement]] or [[entertainment]]; and in [[warfare]]; a [[plane]].

